author: {'steamid': '76561198965927572', 'num_games_owned': 47, 'num_reviews': 16, 'playtime_forever': 1016, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 4, 'playtime_at_review': 1016, 'last_played': 1711863962}
review:
I remember playing this a few times because I liked how it was basically "GTA but with a post-soviet city map", but the gameplay was so bland I forgot about it... But now that I remembered this game, it turns out the devs killed it. Even though it runs on Unity and could most likely run with just the files on the installed client, but oh well... 

Games as a "service" amirite?

Anyway, just get Garry's Mod and grab one of the many open world maps and cars on the workshop. You'll get better gunplay, movement and graphics that this game ever had right out of the box. Sadly, the post-soviet feeling city cannot be so easily replaced, but oh well...

I knew the production team had worked hard, but bugs were still popping up, and my mind exploded
-The wheels will lose their stickers after the car explodes
-The car does not have a highlight map and a normal map
- At least add a normal map and highlight map to the city
-Some trees in the distance that turn on SSAO will have black edges
-When driving, a car will suddenly brush up in the distance
- Some streets lose a short white line in the distance (?) Map
-The car feels real to the touch, but the car is as brittle as a paper shell
- The range of the car explosion is ridiculously small, as long as you don't touch the car when it explodes, you can be unharmed
- The sky textures are like a batch of paste after being enlarged by the AI, and there are colored imperfections everywhere
-The UI and font are too paste, the mobile version may be because the resolution is small to look clear
-SSAO is too dark, and there are also SSAO under some grass, which looks very unnatural
-The performance of the car is carved out of a mold, and the speed is adjusted, and the off-road vehicle cannot even go up a small hurdle
-The picture quality of this generation is not as good as that of the previous generation
-Although passers-by have a ped cross-dress function, but this is done very badly, normal people who will wear a mask to go out ah?
-Watching passers-by from a distance can be very stiff
- The protagonist jumps too low, and the distance jumps is ridiculously short
- There is a wear mold at the joint of a train car in one place, and some items with physical effects are also pressed by the car
- Although the pattern of vegetation is understandable, I hope that I can make the vegetation react a little when it touches the vegetation
-Driving some cars is a body that shakes
- Why would I have to spend 300 diamonds to drive my own car?! The mobile version does not come with this
When the -ped hit some obstacles, they would just stand there and sometimes wear molds
- Police will appear immediately when committing a crime, and you will get a Good Citizen Star, whether there are police officers around you or not (only exists in the computer version)
-It also costs 300 gold coins to send the car, and the mobile version is treated too well
- Stickers are a lot like porridge, maybe you can upgrade with AI or find new stickers (I also have a sticker library)
-This operation is like a heifer flying a plane to drink milk, the cow is outrageous, it is recommended to change to:
Get on the bus F, camera mode ~
All in all, the game can still be played with fewer bugs, and it may be unexpectedly fun, but the game has too many bugs, and it also takes up 500MB of my memory

review: This game is a true work of art. The fact that there is essentially no plot, no characters and no objectives whatsoever makes this game a strange liminal sandbox of violence, cars and existential loneliness. Throwing the little russian cars around empty russian streets, jumping the many ramps and memorizing the simple AI of the cops has kept me mildly entertained in a beautiful way for many hours. Ive downloaded this game on mobile, on Mac and now on PC at last, and i always seem to keep coming back, despite the fact there is almost nothing to come back to. Highly Recommended.

author: {'steamid': '76561198880947719', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 1304, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1108, 'last_played': 1676864347}
review:
I don't know how I managed to get this amount of hours on a GTA mobile Russian knock off. All I can say is that it's a masterpiece.

I couldn't play it on my potato phone. The graphics are okay. All the screenshots are real except for the filters and hidden HUD.

The missions are tedious to complete with no real story. But they are easy enough to farm coins. I have no clue how to get gems but I rarely buy stuff so it doesn't matter.

Fair warning, mission 23 is basically impossible. It's broken. The timing is too unforgiving even with the fastest car in the game. It just comes down to luck with traffic and your driving skills.

This game is full of bugs. You fall through the floor regularly.

There isn't much to do on free roam. I love committing vehicular manslaughter on this game. The cops are easy to deal with and the physics are very broken leading to some really funny things. (Both in cars and running over pedestrians)

The NPCs are soulless. You won't feel bad for mercilessly massacring them if you are wondering.

There isn't too much customization when it comes to vehicle and character customization. The NPCs are wearing random combinations of all the items you can buy in the store.

I unfortunately never got to play the multiplayer. People said it was good but It's now closed. It would be cool to have dedicated servers.

This game is basically never updated. I don't even know if the developer/s are still supporting it. I wish they released a third game that isn't made in the awful unity engine.

I've never played the first game and I don't intend to due to the bad reviews and you have to pay for it. This game is free and for what it offers, It's worth it. You have nothing to lose by trying it out. Run some people over and see how ridiculous the physics are. Do some missions to get money and get cool clothes or buy a new car. Something I don't even do. I mainly just steal NPC cars, You have to pay 500 coins to get it delivered (You get minimum 1k coins for completing 1 mission, kinda expensive if you ask me) There is no real advantage to delivering your custom car other than paying 299 coins for temporary nitro.

review:
[h1]Est√° lleno de bugs, el juego es un bug[/h1] 

Te trabas al salir del auto, a veces no podes salir o entrar a los mismos, es posible caerse del mapa y sumergirse en la Matrix de esta parodia rusa del GTA, buena parte de las misiones est√°n bugueadas y se hace o extremadamente dif√≠cil el pasarlas o extremadamente f√°cil, el dise√±ador de las misiones relacionadas a la conducci√≥n debe ser un ingeniero que construye monta√±as rusas (ya dije que el juego es ruso?). La tienda, que se supone que es de donde sacar√≠an ingresos, puesto que el juego es gratis, est√° tan bugueada como el resto del juego. Pens√© que era un mal puerto de la versi√≥n m√≥vil, pero ambos tienen tantos bugs que es m√°s dif√≠cil saber si fue primero el huevo chueco o la gallina chueca, al menos esta versi√≥n no tiene anuncios a cada parpadeo, como la de m√≥viles. A veces no se distingue entre un auto funcional y uno explotado, y si, ya se que intentaste entrar a uno explotado, tambi√©n te habr√°s dado cuenta que los personajes corren como si la naturaleza los llamase, quiz√°s sea as√≠.
En definitiva, este juego que trata de ser similar al GTA es como un Lada a una Chevy Coupe, pero as√≠ como un Lada era barato, este juego es gratuito, y como dice el dicho, "A caballo regalado no se le miran los dientes"... Aunque si este juego fuera caballo seguro no tendr√≠a dientes.

author: {'steamid': '76561198351898440', 'num_games_owned': 111, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 150, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 148, 'last_played': 1596803600}
review:
[h1] 2 / 10 - √à solo un'altro clone malriuscito di un gioco famoso. [/h1]

(Nota: a settembre 2020, gli sviluppatori hanno annunciato di non aver pi√π intenzione di aggiornare la versione Steam del gioco)

√à letteralmente un gioco per Android, esportato per pc (in Unity, File -> Build settings -> PC Standalone -> Build) con minime modifiche fatte giusto per far funzionare i comandi. E lo capirete subito dall'interfaccia del menu principale, dal menu a ruota visualizzato col tasto destro del mouse, e da alcuni pulsanti che non si possono premere (il mouse viene ovviamente usato per la visuale).

Contiene molti errori ortografici che a volte sembrano intenzionali per quanto vengono ripetuti: [i]gaz, weapone, dencity, ditonator, jips, mission complite,[/i] e si potrebbe andare avanti.

Le armi sono a pagamento, cos√¨ come le auto (e le relative verniciature) e i vestiti per il personaggio. Ma non basta comprare l'auto, bisogna anche pagare per farsela consegnare. E a meno che non vogliate spendere soldi reali (c'√® la solita solfa della valuta in-game difficile se non impossibile da ottenere e che si pu√≤ acquistare) dovrete aspettare sempre 30 secondi. E l'auto non arriva realmente consegnata da qualcuno, spawna affianco a voi. Proprio di fianco. Immagino sia stato solo inserito un delay assieme alla finta barra di progresso.

Poi ci sono missioni di "parkour" in cui si segue un percorso di piattaforme in auto. Ho visto gente confondere freerunning, tricking e parkour, ma questo?
E se vi dicessi che bisogna pagare 93$ letteralmente per cadere per terra? O 415$ per lanciarvi dal parabrezza dell'auto?

Ricordo di averlo giocato due anni fa su Android, e non era cos√¨ risibile. Non so se definirlo esattamente un cash grabber, ma √® adatto solo a farsi due risate con qualche amico. Almeno riesce in questo.

review: I played this a BIT on My iPad awhile back, as far as I can tell nothing has changed, it's a game with potential, but pay-to-win microtransactions They WANT Us to make, ruin that potential... You can run around, steal a Lambo, paint it, put vinyls on it, etc. (which cost in game $), BUT You cannot KEEP it, unless You bought it from the menu, & once You buy clothes, hair, accessories, plus weapons when You start, You don't even have enough $ for the cheapest car, much less a cool one. I have never tried to play online on either platform, from what I've read every mobile gangsta sandbox game is full of cheaters, so I never bother, but offline this game COULD be nicer, perhaps if You could KEEP cars You stole. ONE last REALLY annoying thing about this game is the cars get damage about 1,000x faster then on any other game from this genre, so updates to let Us shoot while driving mean nothing if cops can blow up the car in 5 seconds flat!

review:
Honestly one of the best games I've played in years, this game has one of the best communities on steam even thought most of the players are under the age of 12 and from Russian its still very fun just like its gameplay. Speaking of which this game is one of if not best open world experience you will get ever and the fact that is free is crazy to me. This game makes triple A companies look trash like RockStar with there shitty games like GTA 5, this game graphically wise gameplay wise and communities wise throws GTA 5 out of the window with how fucking good it is, and its FREE honestly this game deserves to be $80 as the experience you get can last up 20 hours with endless missions and things to do with your friend. I highly recommend this game zero flawes what so ever and still one of my favourite games to this day.

- runs on any potato
- huge servers filled with Brazilian teenagers

10/10, would invest an hour of my Sunday again

author: {'steamid': '76561198118064038', 'num_games_owned': 266, 'num_reviews': 63, 'playtime_forever': 69, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 69, 'last_played': 1582132558}
review:
Ragazzi io per descrivere questo gioco avrei solo una parola in mente ed inizia con "Tumor", l'altra lettera potreste indovinarla voi. 
Inizierei con il parlarvi della grafica e del gameplay di questo magnifico, inimitabile , ineguagliabile PEZZO D'ARTE MODERNA di un gioco.
La grafica √® unica nel suo genere, proprio come i crimini che avvengono in Brasile, un putiferio di texture e modelli scaraventati a destra e a manca che NON potrete dimenticare, anche perch√® questo incubo vi inseguir√† nei vostri sogni come un poliziotto che vede un nero. 
Parliamo ovviamente del gameplay, porco IL signore, sperando voi capite di chi io stia parlando, una cosa indescrivibile. Tu spawni sempre nello stesso punto , al massimo spostato di 30 cm da prima, in mezzo a 4000 altre persone che verranno costantemente spawnkillate dal Russo o Arabo del cazzo che ha le armi SHOPPATE visto che la maggior parte costano soldi veri all'infinito ed oltre. Se in qualche maniera riuscite ad uccidere il terrorista, o il sovietico a vostro gradimento, rubategli le armi e aspettate che qualche poveraccio spenda soldi per farsi portare la sua automobile, ed iniziate a scarrellare con la vostra arma automatica contro il veicolo. In non-meno di 2 secondi salter√† per aria, rendendo la sua vita una schifezza proprio come tu che hai deciso di giocarci per pi√π di 15 minuti (me compreso). Fatt√≤ ci√≤, direi che il singleplayer per farmare quelle due monete in croce √® una schifezza pure quello, complimenti per aver accatastato 4 robacce a caso e averlo messo su Steam, piattaforma morente. Molto coraggiosi, adesso mangiatevi una sedia.
Voto finale 100/100 IGN "no regrets" e anche "no spaghett"

review:
mi resumen:
puntos positivos:
-buena jugabilidad
-buenos graficos
-muy buen mapa y muy extenso
-el juego es muy accesible ya que es multiplataforma, pero deben de ser compatibles con los de (ios)
-(tiene mucho futuro) :D

puntos negativos:
-servers con mucho ping
-pocas armas 
-muy dificil conseguir dinero y diamantes
-no puedes apuntar con las armas
-escases de municion para las armas
-el intefaz es dificil de manejar para cambiar de arma

-precios muy elevados en general de todo

author: {'steamid': '76561198397700199', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 28, 'playtime_forever': 421, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 289, 'last_played': 1576550156}
review:
I have thoroughly enjoyed some aspects of this game which is the driving and some of the physics involving car crashes and chases(the tires do not come apart though I wish they did).  however there are many more things that need to be corrected first is the microtransaction system.  some cars and weapons cannot even be accessed through grinding which can be really problematic and make the game developers of this game appear to be greedy.  

this can be fixed by allowing cash and diamonds for each car and weapon and clothing therefore allowing players to grind for the cars and weapons if they want to and if they want to get their weapons faster they can use gems.

second the multiplayer system is incredibly broken.  meaning you have to burn large amounts of cash you grinded for in a single multiplayer server to spawn your cars and get weapons.  

there needs to badly be a traffic system and cops for multiplayer that way players can access cars and kill cops for weapons instead of other players waiting to get them when they are vulnerable.  

third is the level system and map design and the graphics of the game altogether.  they need to be improved slightly but not too much to where performance is an issue.  what needs to be improved is the buildings, trees and other objects that float (yes they all are floating in mid-air), the player desperately needs a way to flip his or her car(so far you cannot flip your car) and when you get out of a car sometimes you will clip through the map... yeah funny but it needs to be fixed.   Also the cash amount you receive from missions needs to be slightly higher like 20,000 to 25,000 is good enough.

if you think I am wrong go ahead and play it for yourself.  its free to play if you haven't noticed and takes up less than one gig of space.

Also if all of these things are fixed I will change my perspective on this game.  I don't want to spread hate I just want to provide constructive criticism.

review: Even though it makes fun to mess around with other people and friends, the game is far away from being good. Many things were not thought through (for example the rocks are pretty bad placed). You can find way to many hackers by playing along. If i think about it, the entier multiplayer isn't thought through cause its basically you gambling if the person near you has a heart or not and will randomly kill you (and that can sometimes well be for the entire time youre playing on that specific server hes on too). Also the gamemodes are, like i said (except for the single player (its nothing special but it atleast works)) pretty bad and it seems like many, if not everyone of them, is not finished. some are not even in the game yet! There werent many updates in months (if not years!) so i dont think the developer/s will do something against it. It could be more fun if the game would get more love and time by the developers but as it is right now i would rate this game 2/10 without friends and 3/10 if you play it with friends.

author: {'steamid': '76561198060132514', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 19, 'playtime_forever': 50, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 50, 'last_played': 1567443888}
review:
I downloaded the game because it was free and had "simulation" tag on it... 
After an hour i just couldn't play any longer
I started with the missions, which are quite interesting, every second mission is a parkour mission (you have to drive with your car through some obstacles) and every 5th or so is a race.
You have 128 missions, but after 13 i couldn't handle another parkour
For whatever reason the gas and brake/backwards buttons are reversed (controller) and it takes some time to get used to it, or you can map the whole controller with your own settings you would like to use.
For a free game you can actually still have some fun. The game has a multiplayer option, so you could mess around with your friends.. for an hour.

author: {'steamid': '76561198037888956', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 18, 'playtime_forever': 441, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 379, 'last_played': 1574527995}
review:
Je le conseille parce que c'est un petit jeu gratuit qui se t√©l√©charge et installe en 2 minutes m√™me pas. 

Bah pour un petit jeu .. il envoi tout de m√™me. Une map tr√®s grande aussi.
Certes la communaut√© peut ne pas √™tre amical, voir mature en serveur RP (dont l'avantage est l'interdiction d'arme, ce qui rend √©gaux tout le monde m√™me s'ils RP pas)

J'ai entendu des choses concernant la conduite du jeu, mais √† mon avis la conduite rivalise avec beaucoup de jeux m√™me AAA, c'est surtout au clavier que c'est dur (ce que j'utilise) car en appuyant sur "Z" je dose pas le champignon et donc je gal√®re. C'est comme IRL, tu appuis une fois, ta caisse avance si tu l√¢che elle d√©c√©l√®re (elle garde au d√©but la vitesse d'acc√©l√©ration, puis au fur et √† mesure la vitesse ralenti) , 
les joueurs de maintenant veulent du instant... pff (t'appuis t'avance, si tu l√¢che le bouton la voiture s'arr√™te net, voir la vitesse diminue consid√©rablement : irr√©aliste).
J'ai aussi vu en commentaire, comme quoi en vue capot on peut pas tourner la cam√©ra .. mais omg,tu mets la vue 1√®re personne et tu peux ! , On peut pas tourner la cam vue capot sur Grand Turismo non plus hein ..

De plus les d√©g√¢ts en voiture sont r√©ussi, exemple : Je prend un tremplin, la voiture tombe en piqu√© vers le bas, BAM le par-choc avant d√©truit (pas comme dans GTA avec le contr√¥le en l'air magique .. ). Si vous prenez ne serait-ce qu'un d√©cors pouvant faire office de dos-d'√¢ne en acc√©l√©rant, il y a une chance pour qu'une partie de la voiture reste sur la route, sans vous.

Ce que je fais pour m'y amuser : Serveur RP, je me prend une voiture, je met la vue premi√®re personne ou vue classique derri√®re le perso, et je roule tranquille sur la bonne voie routi√®re, j'ai remarqu√© que les gens en font de m√™me, du coup on arrive √† reproduire une circulation (certes minime) style russe ^^ Oui parce que le fameux road rage est le sport f√©tiche en jeu :D

Essayez, avec des amis si possible pour le fun et une langue commune, et faites vous une id√©e.

author: {'steamid': '76561198136052770', 'num_games_owned': 418, 'num_reviews': 31, 'playtime_forever': 6, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 6, 'last_played': 1546065030}
review:
This is probably the worst game I have ever played. First of all, it is made for mobile devices and shouldn't even be on Steam, and second of all, it looks like I'm streaming my phone to my PC because the graphics are so bad.

Controller support is a joke. Every other game I have played has been fine with my controller, but when I am in a server, my character keeps running in a circle and the camera won't stop rotating. Literally unplayable (in a non-ironic way). 

I'm not sure why this game was even made. It has no purpose or reward for playing, and I constantly feel like my IP is being stolen.

author: {'steamid': '76561198043925861', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 7, 'playtime_forever': 14, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 14, 'last_played': 1542404167}
review:
Erstmal das Positive. Die Grafik ist f√ºr ein Indyspiel durchaus OK. Vergleichbar vielleicht mit dem ersten Gothic. Das gl√§nzte ebenfalls nicht unbedingt durch die Grafik aber einem genialen Spiel. Es gibt allerdings noch viele Fehler wie schwebende Kr√§ne oder √§hnliches.

Die Welt ist auch relativ gro√ü und auch Abwechslung ist vorhanden. 

Allerdings bietet das Spiel, zumindest im Singleplayer, mal gar nichts. Man kann auf Personen schie√üen und nichts passiert. Naja, irgendwann fallen sie tot um, aber sie gehen weiter und auch andere Passanten reagieren gar nicht auf eine Schie√üerei. Die Polizei st√∂rt es nicht einmal im geringsten wenn man vor deren Nase ein Auto klaut indem man den Fahrer raus pr√ºgelt nach reiner GTA-Manier.

Autos haben schon ein Schadensmodel und die Werkstatt funktioniert ebenfalls beim reparieren und umlakieren. Die Farbwahl beim lackieren der Felgen darf man zwar bezahlen aber nichts passiert.

Das ist eigentlich aber auch schon alles was bei dem Spiel funktioniert. 

Was mir aber extrem negativ aufgefallen ist. Es gibt bereits zwei W√§hrungseinheiten in dem Spiel, eine davon mit Echtgeld zu bezahlen. Genau an der Stelle sieht man schon wo der Hase hin laufen soll. In das √úbel das die Spieleindustrie immer mehr und mehr infiziert. Die Gier nach noch mehr Kohle. Weil ja f√ºr ein durchschnittliches Spiel 49 Euro nicht ausreichend sind muss man nat√ºrlich noch Ingame-Payments einf√ºhren. 

F√ºr mich ist letzteres das endg√ºltige KO-Kriterium f√ºr dieses Spiel.

Es h√§tte viel werden k√∂nnen. Das Potenzial ist da. Respekt an eine wahrscheinlich recht kleine Programmierergruppe die immerhin eine recht gute Welt gezaubert hat. Aber leider habt ihr noch nichts abgeliefert au√üer das ihr eure Geldquelle schon eingebaut habt.

author: {'steamid': '76561198274296955', 'num_games_owned': 315, 'num_reviews': 92, 'playtime_forever': 48, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 31, 'last_played': 1554068464}
review:
Well..... this is certainly....... something. So, MadOut2.... is an iOS port, as I do remember playing it on there. That alone should basically tell you the quality of the game, but hey, I feel that I should make this review anyway based on my first thoughts, so here. 

Story: Basically, from what I gathered, you are coming back from prison to the city. That's all, and you do crime. 

Gameplay: Just looking at the game should tell you that this is a GTA ripoff, just not as good. You have all the GTA stuff like stealing cars from proportionally broken people, killing people for no reason (you can't even get money from it), and more. So what does this game do different? Well, from what I can tell, nothing. All you have is a new undetailed map that shows off how it is basically unfinished, and is willing to remove certain GTA mechanics, like good customization (There is literally only around 2 hair options, and no gender options either, which seems..... you fill the blanks.) One thing this game has going for it is online. I did not check it out yet, so who knows how this works out. Also, touching water kills you, how else would it work, of course it will instantly kill you! So no, there is no underwater secrets like that UFO thing in GTA 5. However, despite all this, it plays..... not horribly actually. The controls work fine and do what they need, except for A button actions, as for some reason, the A button pulls up the menu and I don't know why. Kinda awkward. So yeah, if you like GTA and don't have the money for the real deal..... then maybe get the money, as this might not be what you are looking for honestly.

Graphics and Presentation: Let's get this out of the way: The game has a TON of Engrish, and this is because I presume the developers are Russian. This can be proven by how all in game street signs are in Russian. Also, the trailer has Russian text so yeah..... still, some Engrish is just.... wow. Like, Gas is spelled "Gaz," among others. You can probably find a ton of Engrish, but I won't really be doing that. I need to do graphics. Anyway, the graphics are.... undetailed. It doesn't look horrible, but you can tell it's an iOS game. It has PS2 like textures and many models have missing polygons and car damage is just...... terrible, using the stock Unity car damage. For all those who want to make a car game using Unity, don't use a stock damage set, they suck. Animations are also awkward, and are disproportional and broken at times. Yeah, quality was not a thing here.

Sound and Soundtrack: This game has music? Well, it all sucks anyway, I won't waste time here with that, you can probably guess the quality. Sounds are also very stock and bland. Just, no.

Replayability: It is open world, so I guess there's that? There is the online, so you can play with friends, but knowing this game, it probably won't let you lock a lobby so that only friends can join. There isn't much to do in the world anyway, just drive. Now, in GTA 5, there are many minigames you can do, like Tennis or Golf, and to other things like Triathlons and such. This game has nothing, and although there is 11 chapters of single player content, you'll get bored.

Final Thoughts: Well, this is an awkward thing. I have so many complaints about this game, and I hope the devs keep this game updated so the issues can be fixed. However, in it's current form, I think this game deserves this score. However, blah blah blah, you get it, opinions, yadda yadda, get to the score. Anyway, based on my experience, MadOut2 BigCityOnline gets a 4/10 with a side of a 5 Star Wanted level. This is a shameless GTA ripoff without what made GTA fun. There are to many complaints against the working gameplay that prevents a recommendation. Yeah, it is free, but how much is that really a factor? It's just bland and uninspired. Even on iOS, it was bland. It's probably also on Andriod, but I would also recommend against it. Now, devs, there is still a way to fix this, and I have some tips:
[list]
[*]Make the world have more stuff to do, while making the game look nicer
[*]Make sure that the character customization has better options
[*]Add more gameplay mechanics
[*]Make it more unique
[*]Don't use the stock Unity damage system
[*]Make the humans look like humans
[*]And more
[/list]
I hope you take my considerations into guarantee.

review:
Knowing two people who owned this before it went free, this was a neat if overpriced and kind of janky GTA clone. But of course this got the same treatment as their original Big City game, and now everything is locked behind a paywall long after release. You don't even start with an owned car, once you buy that with "free" credits you're nearly broke - you won't even have enough left for a basic paintjob let alone tuning. Want to play a mission? Cool. Buy it. Want to do anything other than aimlessly drive around an empty world? Cool, give us more money.

Asset flip developers are bad, but so are these guys trying to carve up PC games into mobile gimme more sims.

author: {'steamid': '76561198164431395', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 435, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 280, 'last_played': 1531813902}
review: Wow a beautiful GTA like game for iOS and Android, what?!?! Wait its on steam too?! Even Better! I was wrong. Sure the game is fun on mobile devices, but thats because the game is actually easy to pick up off the App Store (thats right guys, its free on mobile!). But really $25 on steam? Nothing but an easy cash grab for you guys huh? The game doesn't even support crossplatform play. So once you spend the $25 make notes saying that you will only see about 7 people. Due to its high price range you wont be seeing much players on multiplayer (lets be real the game doesn't even have a story mode so whos going to play single player anyways?). Its sad that you have a top of the notch price, but the game isnt even premium built (more as an early access stage). I cant say the same thing for mobile because its actually free and HAS players. Please do not waste your time on this purchase until the price drops or it becomes free. At this rate I should even be refunding the game but I do see potential (from playing the mobile version), so just keep the $25 I gave you. But this will be a thumbs down until you make the game cost less or actually free so we can have a full game.

review: This game has potential, and can be a little fun. But it should not be sold the way it is. The price they are asking is ludicrous. The game is completely unfinished, the controls are buggy with an xbox one controller and there are menu bugs that make it really difficult to remap the keys. The game should be sold as an early pre release title either for free or for a couple bucks, nothing more. It's a blatant money grab to ask 25 dollars for a game like this that is the quality of a free mobile game. Even on sale for 17.49 there is no justification for that price. I'm not saying the devs can't turn this into a nice product, in fact the recent update added A LOT to the game but right now is far from the time to sell it as a finished product let alone for this insane price.

author: {'steamid': '76561198029228358', 'num_games_owned': 365, 'num_reviews': 68, 'playtime_forever': 533, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 370, 'last_played': 1580265042}
review:
Quite a cheesy yet interesting game i do like the physics , it looks like one of those android games you can get on google play but i do enjoy it , its very cheap as well

pros: Arcade Style racing game very easy it feels familiar in handelling
it has numerous modes 4 distinct modes, Death race, Normal 1 lap race or sprint,  and time attack, and missions  marked by the big M for mackster
Open world and you can get vehicles off the streets or you can buy some right at the far end of the map
good graphics for unity and an indy developer
feels like my gmod sandbox partially
Love the ai perfectly programmed to mimic russias driving habits i find it quite funny.
any car you have nicked and you like it can be saved in the garage
hint there is a supercar hidden in the game that can spawn in the streets thats the best car in the game so far.

Quirkiness: It has badly translated russian to english if the devs want a guy to fix the ui i could so it says good english.


overall:

I am overall impressed that madout city  done by a small team or one dev has been done very well I commend the person who has done madout city cheap and Fun
i expect to have hours of fun on this and its low on hdd space as well only 133 mb

Future development for devs take note

Multiplayer,(recommended but hosted on steam multiplayer servers)
More Garages to Repair your vehicle spray your vehicle etc
prehaps release some performance shops to futhure enhance your cars modified and unmodified 
i would like to extreme tune the lada 2101
More customization for vehicles start off with a range of spoilers at the bodyshop
The garage you start with needs improvement and rear wall at the garage with a hole for your player to go in and then grab your car

Your unique car liveries need to save when you right click and click car_paint because everytime i save it and get it repaired it reverts back to the old livery.(well i did get the supercar which is already tuned)
if performance upgrades where released to make your car go faster i would so be nicking that lada in game the lada 2101 and fully tune it with performance upgrades
needs some hardbass like a true slav.

for people reading my review: Go buy it and see for yourself guys and gals its actually worth it


UPDATE2018: The Cars are Now customizable And a hellla alot of fun Made it 10x As playable and worth it havent seen the performence upgrades yet but I will look into it the game has gone from good to much better keeping it installed ready for use
The devs Listened and i am Increasingly happy with there product
